note.label: Note
note.p: For information about Prints and Photographs Division collections and services, see the Prints & Photographs Division's Reading Room Home Page.

The following terms have been used to index the description of this collection in the Library's online catalog. They are grouped by name of person or organization, by subject or location, and by occupation and listed alphabetically therein.

userestrict.head: Restrictions
userestrict.p: Publication may be restricted. For information see the Katherine Young Collection (LOTs 13309 & 13310) Rights and Restriction Informationpage.

altformavail.head: Additional form available
altformavail.p: Digitized images of some items in the collection and their associated identifying information are available through the Prints & Photographs Online Catalog, by searching using the call number "LOT 13309."

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Researchers wishing to cite this collection should include the following information: Library of Congress, Prints & Photographs Division, Courtesy Katherine Young [reproduction number, e.g., LC-USZ62-12345].

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: Formal portraits of national and international figures. Diplomats, statesmen, and political figures are featured prominently throughout the LOT. Includes some portraits of U.S. Supreme Court justices, architects, and artists. Also one portrait of Alice Acheson and one of Mary Rockefeller (Mrs. Nelson Rockefeller).

arrangement.head: Organized/Arranged
arrangement.p: Photographs are organized by size into two subdivisions. LOT-13309-1 has the smaller prints designated (F); LOT 13309-2 has the larger prints designated (H). A single alphabetical index for both sizes serves as the container list
